who I was talking about.

884
00:41:28,031 --> 00:41:30,934
Look, you know I always
got your back on this stuff.

885
00:41:30,967 --> 00:41:35,238
Apparently, Nikki and Sarah
had a conversation about you

886
00:41:35,272 --> 00:41:36,573
that-that day you weren't in,

887
00:41:36,606 --> 00:41:39,443
and, uh, Nikki said
she just thought of you

888
00:41:39,476 --> 00:41:41,778
like her little brother
or, you know,

889
00:41:41,812 --> 00:41:43,013
and she, like, friend-zoned you.

890
00:41:43,046 --> 00:41:45,248
And-and-and look,
that may suck to hear,

891
00:41:45,282 --> 00:41:46,817
but I just think
you got to know because,

892
00:41:46,850 --> 00:41:49,419
I-I don't know, I think she has
some kind of ill intentions

893
00:41:49,453 --> 00:41:51,788
or something freaking mental
is going on, man.

894
00:41:51,822 --> 00:41:53,590
And maybe Sarah's jealous
and made that up,

895
00:41:53,623 --> 00:41:56,359
but, like, even if you take
that out of the equation,

896
00:41:56,393 --> 00:41:59,463
this is strange, dude.

897
00:41:59,496 --> 00:42:01,665
It's like Nikki snapped
into a different person.

898
00:42:01,698 --> 00:42:04,601
Sh-She's all of a sudden
infatuated with you.

899
00:42:04,634 --> 00:42:06,670
♪ ♪

900
00:42:20,650 --> 00:42:22,519
Everything okay?

901
00:42:28,425 --> 00:42:30,794
(voice trembling):
Nikki, do you...

902
00:42:32,763 --> 00:42:34,731
What?

903
00:42:35,866 --> 00:42:37,834
Never mind.

904
00:42:37,868 --> 00:42:40,370
I have something for you.

905
00:42:40,403 --> 00:42:42,572
-What is it?
-Um...

906
00:42:50,914 --> 00:42:52,516
What is it?

907
00:42:54,117 --> 00:42:56,419
Open it.

908
00:43:01,691 --> 00:43:04,561
It's a... it's a tiger's eye.

909
00:43:04,594 --> 00:43:06,863
-Wow.
-It was my mom's,

910
00:43:06,897 --> 00:43:08,999
and then it was mine.

911
00:43:09,032 --> 00:43:14,538
It's supposed to bring you
confidence and willpower, so...

912
00:43:14,571 --> 00:43:16,807
now you can be a food critic.

913
00:43:19,543 --> 00:43:21,344
Why are you giving it to me?

914
00:43:21,378 --> 00:43:25,382
Bear, I love you
so, so, so, so, so much.

915
00:43:25,415 --> 00:43:27,717
I don't think I could live
without you.

916
00:43:32,122 --> 00:43:35,325
You love me more
than anyone in the world?

917
00:43:39,129 --> 00:43:41,698
(chuckling):
Yes, more than anyone.

918
00:43:45,001 --> 00:43:46,570
Nikki.

919
00:43:47,704 --> 00:43:49,406
Yeah?

920
00:43:49,439 --> 00:43:51,408
Does your dad
really have cancer?

921
00:43:51,441 --> 00:43:53,610
♪ ♪

922
00:44:05,889 --> 00:44:07,390
No.

923
00:44:10,727 --> 00:44:13,129
(chuckling):
No, no, no.

924
00:44:13,163 --> 00:44:14,431
What?

925
00:44:14,464 --> 00:44:16,399
No, no, no,

926
00:44:16,433 --> 00:44:18,668
-no, no, no, no, no.
-What?

927
00:44:18,702 --> 00:44:20,437
-Don't do that!
-Nikki. (stammers)

928
00:44:20,470 --> 00:44:22,873
-I thought we were having a
nice date. -(patrons murmuring)

929
00:44:22,906 --> 00:44:24,741
-We-we are. We are. Sit down.
-Why does it matter?

930
00:44:24,774 --> 00:44:28,111
-I thought we were having
a nice date. -We are. We are.

931
00:44:28,144 --> 00:44:29,980
-We are. We are.
-(Nikki crying)

932
00:44:30,013 --> 00:44:32,082
It's okay.

933
00:44:32,115 --> 00:44:34,718
We are. We are.

934
00:44:44,594 --> 00:44:46,630
Then why does it matter?

935
00:44:54,604 --> 00:44:56,006
It doesn't matter to me.

936
00:44:56,039 --> 00:44:58,642
(grunts) Oh, yeah.

937
00:44:58,675 --> 00:45:00,944
(grunting, moaning)

938
00:45:02,612 --> 00:45:05,515
-(Bear grunting)
-Yeah. Uh-huh.

939
00:45:06,217 --> 00:45:08,585
(moaning)

940
00:45:09,953 --> 00:45:11,855
(breathing heavily)

941
00:45:11,888 --> 00:45:14,591
-Oh, that was amazing, baby.
-Yeah.

942
00:45:17,261 --> 00:45:18,929
Yeah.

943
00:45:28,505 --> 00:45:30,740
(takes deep breath)

944
00:45:51,094 --> 00:45:52,696
Nikki?

945
00:46:06,977 --> 00:46:09,546
-NIKKI: Go back to sleep.
-(Bear gasps)

946
